    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="741"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.61/58: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-03T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 3, 2:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2959. Following from [<persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName> at]
                    Archangel.</p>
                <p>1402, September 2, 7 p.m. Embassy and consulate staffs sailing for London on the
                    steamer <hi rend="italic">Kildonan Castle</hi> today except Albert, Flack and
                    myself who expect to leave on or about September 7. See no reason for United
                    States Steamship <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> remaining after my
                    departure.</p>
                <p>Japanese and Serbian Chargé d’Affaires leaving today. Chinese Chargé d’Affaires
                    already gone. French Chargé d’Affaires will remain somewhat longer to demobilize
                    Russian-French legion. On September 1st British Chargé d’Affaires ceased
                    functioning as such either here or with Foreign Office, becoming “Diplomatic
                    Adviser” to Commander-in-Chief <persName>Rawlinson</persName>. Movement of
                    British troops has begun and expected to be completed as planned by September
                    30th. <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
